    "summary": "25+ years experience leading initiatives and developing new business in Strategic Workforce Planning, HR Analytics, HR Strategy, Talent and Knowledge Management. Worked in both consulting and industry in sectors including Professional Services, Oil & Gas, Finance, Pharma and Telecom and IT.\n\nCurrently providing thought leadership developing data and insight driven Strategic, Tactical and Operational Workforce Planning. Maximising growth and profitability through optimisation of the People Value Chain.\n\nSKILLS\nStrong conceptual thinker with a passion for innovation, strategy and people development. Strong analytical and consulting skills, delivered large (< $ 25 Mln) complex projects, demonstrating resilience when under pressure and dealing with ambiguity. Always seeking pragmatic ways to demonstrate immediate and tangible business value. Strong external presence through extensive external networks.\n\nVALUES\nEnjoys working in complex and challenging international environments, with high levels of autonomy and room for new developments. Genuine interest in people, valuing an honest style and personal integrity, with a passion to unlock the power in people. Strongly holds to own personal beliefs, expressing views not necessarily held by the majority. Setting high standards for self and others, prepared to take calculated risk. Rapidly identifies people\u2019s strengths and weaknesses, building and managing strong teams.\n\nMaster's degree in Industrial Design from Delft University.\n\nSpecialties: Human Capital Management, HR Strategy, Workforce Planning, HR Analytics, Talent Management and Knowledge Management\n\n(email: ton.vandijk@chello.nl)",
